                  </hi>. I am a woollen-draper, and live in Surrey-place, Newington Butts. About nine o'clock, on Saturday morning, the 3rd of May, I saw the prisoner come into my shop, take a piece of calico, put it under his arm, and walk off with it—I followed him, and called," Stop thief!"—I saw him drop it, and picked it up—it is my property.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. PAYNE</hi>. <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> Did you see it taken? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I did—I was at the desk, in the middle of the shop—I could see the prisoner, but he could not see me—I am quite sure the person who took it was the person who threw it down.</p>
